description: Hi guys! It bit a bit over a month since I posted first 2020 personal piece so had to catch up and off hours finished another piece. I am attaching some extras of how I put together all elements while working on that piece. Instead of just pure 2d or 3d I call my techniques in my concept art pieces - "Hybrid concept art" - sounds cool haha! But in fact, since a lot of things are back and forth and I build up extra elements to help executing/speed up or make my ideas more accurate the first output render (as you see in attachments) never is the last I use. For mocking things up I use 3dsmax, for more organic assets 3dcoat and Octane for rendering it all out (test and final renders). It relates to both - my professional and personal work, so here is a little behind the scenes with it + of course final painting. Thank you and have a great week! ü§© Follow me on: www.instagram.com/darekzabrock‚Ä¶ www.facebook.com/darek.zabrock‚Ä¶ twitter.com/darekzabrocki MY NEWEST CONCEPT ART SCHOOL PROJECT!!! -------------> focalpointschool.com
